---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words Ending in X — High-Scoring Strategy Guide (2026)" description="Master words ending in X for Scrabble. WAX (13pts), FOX (13pts), JINX (18pts), ONYX (14pts), TAX (10pts) and 50+ more. X-ending placement strategy inside." keywords="scrabble words ending in x, words ending in x scrabble, x ending words, wax scrabble, fox scrabble, jinx scrabble, onyx scrabble, high scoring x words">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words Ending in X — High-Scoring Strategy Guide","description":"Master words ending in X for Scrabble. WAX (13pts), FOX (13pts), JINX (18pts), ONYX (14pts) and 50+ more ranked by score.","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-x"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best Scrabble words ending in X?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Top words ending in X include JINX (18pts), ONYX (14pts), WAX (13pts), FOX (13pts), BOX (12pts), MIX (12pts), RELAX (12pts), and TAX (10pts). Short X-ending words score high because X is worth 8 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why are words ending in X so valuable in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Words ending in X place the X tile (8 points) at the end of the word, which often lands on premium squares as you extend across the board. X-ending words also can't easily be extended by opponents (few words start with X), making them defensively strong."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can words ending in X be extended with S?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most words ending in X cannot simply add S to pluralize (you can't play FOXS or BOXS). The plural of FOX is FOXES, BOX is BOXES. This makes X-ending words defensively powerful — opponents can't just add S to your word for easy points."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in X — High-Scoring Strategy Guide</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Words ending in X are some of the most strategically powerful plays in Scrabble. X at the end means your opponent can't easily hook an S onto your word, making these plays defensively excellent while scoring 8+ from the X alone. Here's your complete guide.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X tile value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JINX top score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">50+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X-ending words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">No S-hook</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Defensive</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 3-Letter Words Ending in X</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">WAX — 13 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">W(4)+A(1)+X(8). A coating or to polish. Common and high-scoring.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">FOX — 13 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">F(4)+O(1)+X(8). A wild canid. Same score as WAX with different tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">BOX — 12 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">B(3)+O(1)+X(8). A container. Common word, easy to form.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">MIX — 12 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">M(3)+I(1)+X(8). To combine. Another common X-ender.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 4-5 Letter Words Ending in X</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JINX</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ONYX</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RELAX</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AFFIX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ANNEX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LATEX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DETOX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HELIX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More X-Ending Words by Score</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HEX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VEX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FIX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SIX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MAX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">INDEX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">REDUX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">X-Ending Placement Strategy</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">X on premium squares:</span> Place X on a DLS for 16 points from that tile alone. WAX with X on DLS = 21 points. On a TLS, X gives you 24 from one tile. Always aim X toward bonuses.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">No S-hook defense:</span> Words ending in X can't be pluralized with S (no FOXS, BOXS). This means your opponent can't cheaply extend your word. X-enders are the most defensive plays in Scrabble.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Cross-word scoring:</span> X at the end of a word also forms perpendicular words. AX, EX, OX are all valid 2-letter words — so X creates crosswords automatically when touching adjacent letters.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Edge of board play:</span> Place X-ending words along the edge so X sits in the corner or last row. This eliminates hook opportunities entirely — maximum defensive value.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Strategy</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Words ending in X are the <span class="text-white font-medium">most hook-proof plays in Scrabble</span>. Unlike words ending in E, S, or D (which opponents can extend), X-enders lock the board. Combine this defensive strength with the 8-point X value on premium squares for maximum impact.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words for Scrabble — Complete Scoring Guide</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/6-letter-words-with-x/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">6-Letter Words with X — Top Scoring Scrabble Words</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all X-ending words instantly — free solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
